We wanted to thank him today for his incredible work.

236
00:20:52,312 --> 00:21:01,454
So for Life is Strange 1, Jonathan delivered around 30 minutes of music covering eight different themes

237
00:21:01,454 --> 00:21:09,236
dedicated to characters, Max and Chloe, Kate, or to areas of the game, Campus, Blackwell Academy

238
00:21:09,236 --> 00:21:13,417
and to different moods of the game, Golden Hour, alternate realities, The Storm.

239
00:21:13,417 --> 00:21:21,578
Jonathan had to compose something that was enough structured as a whole song and could be used in various ways.

240
00:21:22,499 --> 00:21:26,784
Each theme should be representative of the song if played alone.

241
00:21:26,784 --> 00:21:31,931
Every song can be looked forever without being boring or losing the feeling of the game.

242
00:21:31,931 --> 00:21:39,560
In the end, we made more than 4 hour music remix based on these 13 minutes.

243
00:21:42,682 --> 00:21:45,604
For Life is Strange 2, the story was a road trip.

244
00:21:45,604 --> 00:21:49,007
We knew that we wouldn't be able to reuse the same themes,

245
00:21:49,007 --> 00:21:51,649
so we aimed for much more than the first one,

246
00:21:51,649 --> 00:21:56,072
to cover all of our needs in terms of moods, characters,

247
00:21:56,072 --> 00:21:58,874
and to be able to have an evolution of the music

248
00:21:58,874 --> 00:22:00,215
all along the episodes.

249
00:22:08,708 --> 00:22:12,510
